               <msContents>
                  <summary>F<locus target="#1r">fols. 1r, </locus>-7r፡ Prayer to Mary including a review of martyrs   <locus target="#7r">7r, </locus>-15v:  Prayer of Moses which saved him from Pharoah, ጸሎተ፡ ሙሴ።, Cf. EMML 4106 (X: 43), IES 4239. F<locus target="#15v">15v, </locus>-77v: Ardǝ’t. See Book of Disciples. መጽሐፈ፡ አርድእት፡. Enno Littmann, “Arde`et: The Magic Book of the Disciples.” JAOS 25 (1904) 1–48, arranged in sections (f<locus target="#15v">15v, </locus>-19v; 19v-21v; 21v-27v;  27v-31r; 31r-33v (regarding Psalms); 33v-35r(regarding Psalms); 35r-43r (regarding the owner); 43r-50r (regarding Mary); 50r-52v (regarding Mary); 52v-57r; 57v-61r; 61r-64v; 64v-66v; 67r-68r; 68r-71r; 71r-73r; 73r-76r; 76r-77v. Some of the sections are marked in later hands and different colors of ink for the days of the week: Monday (52v), Tuesday (57v), Wednesday (<locus target="#61r">61r, </locus>), Thursday (<locus target="#64v">64v, </locus>), Friday (f<locus target="#67r">67r, </locus> and 71r), Saturday (<locus target="#73r">73r, </locus>,  covered by miniature), Sunday (<locus target="#76r">76r, </locus>).  F<locus target="#77v">77v, </locus>-78v: Image of Saint George, Mälk‘a Giyorgis, መልክአ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡. Not listed in Répertoire. EMIP 240, incipit: ተማኅፀንኩ: በቀዊሞትከ: በቅድመ: ዱድያኖስ: ንጉሥ: . ., incomplete at the end. F<locus target="#79r">79r, </locus>-84r: Office Prayers, Kidan za-nagh, ኪዳን፡ ዘነግህ፡, arranged for the parts of the day: morning (<locus target="#79r">79r, </locus>), midday (<locus target="#81v">81v, </locus>), and evening (<locus target="#83r">83r, </locus>). <locus target="#84v">84v, </locus>. Magnificat. F<locus target="#85r">85r, </locus>-86v: Image of the Savior of the World, Mälk‘a Mädḫane Aläm, መልክአ፡ መድኃኔ፡ ዓለም፡. Répertoire 164.  F<locus target="#7r">7r, </locus> and passim mention the owner, ሀብተ ማርያም. F<locus target="#84r">84r</locus> and passim, mention another original owner, ወልደ ሃይማኖት. </summary>
